@Buildings1772 I used to ask myself the same question. It is ALWAYS 90º, &#39;cause it doesn&#39;t have anything to do with &quot;lag&quot; or &quot;phase&quot; (even though we might call it that). It has to do with torque and angular momentum.
The blades are spinning on a plane and whichever cyclic command you give it, you are applying force on a 90º angle from that plane. Torque will cause the existing angular momentum to change its direction.
